node.text:
Congratulations to our newest Gabb Ambassador, Ava Johnson! As a level 10 gymnast, Ava works hard every day to push herself to reach her goals. She truly lives beyond the screen with her Gabb Phone, focusing on what she loves to do and not wasting her time with tech. Her passion to inspire other kids to do the same is contagious! We're so excited to have you as a Gabb Ambassador, Ava!

Thank you to our VIP partner @provobeach, @brighamyounguniversity's @cosmo_cougar, and @bloxdesserts for helping us celebrate Ava and all those who support her!

At age 15, Samantha Gordon was honored with the NFL’s first ever “Game Changer” award for her stand-out career on the football field. She began playing tackle football with the boys at age 9, and later pioneered the world’s first all-girls tackle football league. Since then, she’s been featured on a Wheaties Box, an NFL commercial, and a Nike commercial shown during the 91st Academy Awards. Do you think she accomplished all that sitting around staring at her phone? No way. Sam wakes up early and trains hard, and that’s what gives her an edge.
.
.
.
